&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="linenos linenodiv"&gt;&lt;a href="https://dg-pb.github.io/posts/pythons-try-finally/#rest_code_67fba88f92814a929037b08fc5b203d9-36"&gt;&lt;code data-line-number="36"&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class="code"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;a id="rest_code_67fba88f92814a929037b08fc5b203d9-36" name="rest_code_67fba88f92814a929037b08fc5b203d9-36"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;             &lt;span class="k"&gt;break&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;So does it need to be deprecated? Or is even issuing a warning needed?
I would vote for not. Why?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="arabic simple"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Most of languages that faced this issue handled it with linters.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Design, although has not been frequently used, is elegant and logical.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Faulty usage can be addressed by stronger emphasis and education.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;It is possible that with more education and time it will be picked up and used more often. In the right way.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
